layout.p:
Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 33;
                                                  written lines: 32; Uniform layout. Double pricking for major lines, in outer and inner margins, quire by quire. Complete ruling by plummet (each bifolium on both sides). Last written line within ruling. Graphic filler at the end of line. Masorah magna often written in the form of figures, animals and patterns; otherwise it occupies three lines in the upper margin and two in the lower margin.
